itemDescription: English rugby union and rugby league footballer

wikipedia_page.main: Walter Jesse Jackson (16 March 1870 – 1 December 1958) was an English rugby union and professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1890s. He played representative level rugby union (RU) for the British Isles, and England, and at club level for Gloucester, and Halifax, as a forward, or wing, and club level rugby league (RL) for Halifax (Heritage No. 9), as a forward.
